The House of Representatives Special Committee on Constitution Review Zonal Public Hearing scheduled to take place in Owerri, Imo State, has been suspended till further notice. The hearing at the Owerri Centre, which was supposed to host Imo and Abia States, was scheduled for Tuesday, 1st and Wednesday, 2nd June, 2021. A statement by the Deputy Speaker and Chairman, House Special Committee on Constitution Review, Ahmed Idris Wase, on Sunday announced the suspension. Although no reason was given for the suspension, it was gathered it may not be unconnected with the issue of insecurity. “The Committee regrets any inconveniences this might cause our esteemed invited guests, stakeholders and the general public,” Wase said.